data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**EF Core 11 fully removes sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider.** In .NET 10, you could opt in to sync-over-async; in .NET 11 that opt-in is gone. Every synchronous call **always throws** — no workaround.

Your four methods all break:

```csharp
// ❌ All of these throw in EF Core 11 + Cosmos
_context.Products.ToList();
_context.Products.First(p => p.Id == id);
_context.Products.Count();
_context.SaveChanges();
```

**Fix — convert to async:**

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

All callers up the chain must also become `async`/`await`. This is the only fix — there is no opt-in to restore sync behavior in EF Core 11.
